Worried by the rate of insecurity in the society, the All Progressives Party (APC), has called on parents to ensure proper upbringing of their, who would contribute towards of the society. Speaking during the naming ceremony of his son in Karshi-Abuja at the weekend, the APC state secretary for the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Hon. Hashismu Angama, attributed most crime in the society to poor parental upbringing of children. Angama pointed out that the growing rate of crime in the FCT and Nigeria in general can also be attributed to the types of friends children mingle with, adding that even a well brought up child could be corrupted by the society through the type of company they keep. “That is why we are calling on parents to train their children properly and guide them in the ways of life, the type of friends they keep, what they read and watch on televisions, because, this things can easily corrupt a good child. “The rate of crime we are experiencing today in the FCT and the entire Nigeria, did not just start yesterday or today. It started years back through the upbringing of the children, who grew up to be controlled by the violence in the society and they decided to live by it. “Our prayer is that as we are working towards controlling the rate of criminality in the society. Parents should also contribute their little quota by training their children to work in the right path, associate with good company that impact positively in their lives.” The secretary also called on residents of the FCT to always be their brother’s keepers, by being vigilant and to report any strange gathering or movement in their communities to the appropriate security agencies for prompts actions.